bibdata.title: Create a list of MARC fields that are included in the keyword index of Blacklight

comments.body: I believe we have done this. Please confirm.

@mzelesky and I added detailed documentation about the marc fields we index in Orangelight. 

Phrase searches generally take precedence in keyword searches.
General order of priority for keyword searching:
1. Title
2. Author
3. Subject
4. Standard numbers

Documentation links: 
https://lib-confluence.princeton.edu/display/ALMA/Alma+-+Blacklight
https://lib-confluence.princeton.edu/display/ALMA/MARC+fields+indexed+in+Blacklight
https://lib-confluence.princeton.edu/display/ALMA/MARC+fields+used+for+facets

In the Orangelight meeting on 9/22/2022 we discussed this issue and decided to talk to DLS on what would help them and be consistent with suppressed item workflows in Pulfalight. https://docs.google.com/document/d/1GxpYrcRc6w3kMFU1XU6CEpnumFzvxFrj2GkCq_XvoWw/edit#heading=h.2n9tc3jqfuku

I think this PR represents the end goal we'd like to reach, but adding the backward compatibility code and the rake task will make it even more complicated. Instead, I'm going to make smaller PRs that only migrate single fields. After the migrations, either this PR can be revived, or the same work can be finished in a new, simpler PR that just removes the backward compatibility and the migration tasks.

So:
- This will stay in draft for a while,
- and it may just end up being closed, if all the work is done in smaller PRs.

princeton_ansible.title: [ealapps] URLs that don't end in a slash give "Something went wrong" error

comments.body:
Note that this also occurs the rest of the directories in the proxy-pass file:
* https://library.princeton.edu/eastasian/newtitles
* https://library.princeton.edu/eastasian/stafftools
* https://library.princeton.edu/eastasian/hishi
* https://library.princeton.edu/eastasian/oclcpinyin
* https://library.princeton.edu/eastasian/assets
* https://library.princeton.edu/eastasian/EALJ
I'd be tempted to see if it worked if the proxy passes in the libwww-proxy-pass.conf has a trailing slash added to the end.

The library-staging versions of these urls also resolve to eal-apps-prod, e.g. 
https://library-staging.princeton.edu/eastasian/shadowfigures resolves to https://eal-apps-prod.princeton.edu/shadowfigures/

Closed by #3586

You must clear your cache or go into an incognito window in order to see the fix. 

Made a separate ticket for the web application firewall for the staging environment - see https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/issues/3589

Thanks for your work on this.  I am still seeing this issue with specific sites that use CAS authentication, e.g. https://library.princeton.edu/eastasian/stafftools/officesupplies.php

Tom

@tventimi - this seems like a separate issue (not related to the slash in the URL).  Could you please confirm that the service url is being set correctly here? https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/ealapps/blob/main/stafftools/gest_report_header.php#L12
@tventimi - the CAS issue is a separate issue - I've created a ticket for it in ealapps - see https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/ealapps/issues/17.
